      <bioghist id="ref6">
         <head>Biographical/Historical Sketch</head>
         <p>Daniel Mazia, cell biologist, was professor emeritus at Stanford University's Hopkins Marine Station at the time of his death in 1996. He earned his Ph.D. at the University of Pennsylvania in 1937. He taught at the University of Missouri (1938-50) and UC Berkeley (1951-79) before joining Stanford's faculty. He was a member of the National Academy of Sciences and the American Academy of Arts and Sciences.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref7">
         <head>Description of the Collection</head>
         <p>Papers include correspondence, research notes, organizational files (including the International Cell Research Organization), course files, publications and reprints, photographs, and videotapes.</p>
      </scopecontent>
